NAME
    RT::Extension::ReportSpam - mark tickets as spam with one click

DESCRIPTION
    A simple extension that works with RT 4.0 and newer and allows users to
    report a ticket as a spam message.

INSTALL
    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make install
    Base configuration
        In RT 4.0 and later, you must enable the plugin by adding
        RT::Extension::ReportSpam to your @Plugins line (or create one) like:

            Set(@Plugins,(qw(RT::Extension::ReportSpam)));

UPGRADING
    RT 3.8
        Users of this extension on RT 3.8 should not upgrade past version 0.03
        of this extension.

HOW TO USE
    Report Spam
        In the ticket display page, you can report the ticket as spam by clicking
        "S".

        Or clicking menu "Tools->Spam->Recent" to get all the recently created
        tickets with status "new" and without owner, you should also click "S" to
        report spam.

        At the same time, if you have rights to delete tickets then they will be
        deleted directly.

    Query All Tickets Reported as Spam
        To find all tickets reported as spam and not deleted you can click menu
        "Tools->Spam->Reported" or use query builder in advanced mode with the
        following query:

            HasAttribute = 'SpamReports'

        to get the tickets reported as spam by others without rights to delete
        tickets.

    Mark a Ticket as Spam
        You can confirm the reports by clicking "S" after querying all tickets reported as spam.
        If you have rights to delete tickets then they will be deleted.

